{
  "texts": [
    "If needed, the use of the index σ or σ will clarify whether we are referring to the microscopic sublattice, or the Chern basis.",
    "Crucially, the Bloch states of Eq. 92 have non-trivial Chern numbers C = στ [32,33,35].",
    "Hence, including the spin degree of freedom, we can group these Chern bands into 'Chern quartets' withC = ±1.",
    "The C = +1 quartet is spanned by |K ↑ A⟩, |K ↓ A⟩, |K ′ ↑ B⟩, |K ′ ↓ B⟩, while the C = -1 quartet is spanned by |K ↑ B⟩, |K ↓ B⟩, |K ′ ↑ A⟩, |K ′ ↓ A⟩.",
    "Generalized Ferromagnets: Exact Slater Determinant Ground StatesThe utility of the Chern basis for addressing many-body physics is most apparent when the chiral ratio κ = w AA /w AB is set to zero."
  ]
}